@{b}ABOUT BLACKARTS@{ub}

BlackArts has the following aims:

  *  @{b}Promote the Amiga by improving the often-overlooked "bottom-end" machines.@{ub}
Most users of other platforms view the Amiga as having a low-resolution grey
screen with ugly black-and-white icons.  We know this isn't the case, but there
are enough Amigas out there which look just like this for that image to persist.

  *  @{b}Provide much-needed support for shareware/freeware programmers.@{ub}
Whilst developing MagicTV, I found it quite impossible to find any information
without spending hours wandering through the Amiga Web Network etc.  I want to
create a centralised network of Amiga programmers willing to help others in
their work.

  *  @{b}Publish shareware and freeware in a standardised, professional manner.@{ub}
Documenting, packaging, putting together a website, and getting others to take
notice of a piece of shareware is hard work.  I want to put together the
resources to make this easier, and offer services to help shareware authors.



